## 4. System components

### 4.1 Customer feedback form (`apps/customer-form`)
- Mobile-responsive web app opened via QR scan
- URL format: `/f/{zone_id}/{token_id}?pos_section=optional`
- No authentication required
- All inputs are tap-based. Zero keyboard input from customer.
- Store name displayed: "The Chennai Silks" (no logo for MVP)
- Target completion: under 45 seconds (billing), under 30 seconds (browse)

### 4.2 Kiosk app (`apps/kiosk`)
- Tablet web app displayed in-store on a single dedicated tablet (MVP: 1 tablet, browse zone only)
- **Auth**: Auto-signs in on boot as the kiosk service account (`kiosk` role). Session persists across reboots. No manual login ever required after IT setup.
- **Three states**: idle, QR display, and offline
- **Visual theme**: dark background throughout. Matches customer form and admin dashboard.
- **Idle state**:
  - Top-left: store name (bold) + section name (muted subtitle) — persistent context
  - Centre: large smiley icon (green outline)
  - Headline: "We'd love your feedback!"
  - Subtitle: "Help us serve you better. It takes less than a minute."
  - Full-width green CTA button: "Tap to share feedback"
  - Footer: "Your response is anonymous" (tiny muted text)
- **QR display state**: on customer tap, calls `mint-token` Edge Function → generates QR → shows live countdown
- **Offline state**: internet connectivity lost → banner shown: "Connection lost. Please try again in a moment." → tap button disabled → polls connectivity every 10 seconds → resumes automatically when reconnected. No broken QRs, no expired tokens issued during outage.
- **Token minting**: always requires active internet. Tokens are minted on-demand at tap time via Edge Function. No pre-minting, no local token generation. QR URL contains `token_id` that must exist in DB before customer's phone validates it.
- **QR display state layout**:
  - Top-left: store name + section name (same as idle, persistent)
  - Top-right: `···` menu (IT/admin access only — not visible to customers)
  - Centre: large QR code block
  - Below QR: "Scan with your phone camera" (bold) + "This QR is just for you" (muted)
  - Countdown line: "Expires in 28s" counting down to 0 in real time
  - On expiry: countdown replaced by "● Expired — returning to welcome" (red dot, red text) → brief pause → returns to idle
- **30-second window**: customer must scan QR within 30 seconds or kiosk returns to idle. Token remains active for 10 minutes total after minting.
- **Token hard expiry**: 10 minutes after mint. If customer has form open but has not submitted by 10 minutes, they are redirected to the timeout page.
- After 30s display timeout or token consumption: auto-return to idle via Supabase Realtime
- Kiosk config embeds: zone_id, product_section (passed to customer form via URL params)
- Fullscreen mode, no browser chrome
- **Admin independence**: admin logging off their dashboard has zero effect on kiosk operation. Kiosk session is a separate Supabase Auth identity.

### 4.3 Admin dashboard (`apps/admin-dashboard`)
- Browser-based web app for Store Admin and MD/Owner
- Role-based views enforced by Supabase RLS
- Store Admin view: zone config, kiosk management, zone dashboard, CSV export, token revocation
- MD/Owner view: cross-zone comparison, section heatmap, trend analysis, CSV export (read-only)

