## 5. Token architecture

Both zones use a unified per-transaction token model. Every QR encodes a unique, single-use token. No shared rotating QR. No cron-based rotation. No timer-based rotation.

### 5.1 Token state machine

```
Minted → Active (instant, on creation)
Active → Used (customer submits feedback)
Active → Expired (TTL elapses without submission)
Active → Revoked (admin manually revokes)
Used, Expired, Revoked = terminal states (no transitions out)
```

### 5.2 Zone-specific token behaviour

| Aspect | Billing zone | Browse zone |
|--------|-------------|-------------|
| QR distribution | Printed on invoice at POS checkout | Displayed on kiosk tablet on customer tap |
| Token trigger | Invoice creation (MVP: admin-generated; future: POS API) | Customer taps "Tap to share feedback" on kiosk |
| Token TTL | 30 minutes hard expiry | 30 seconds (kiosk QR display) → idle reset. 10 minutes hard expiry after token minted. |
| Kiosk display window | N/A | 30 seconds. If not scanned, kiosk returns to idle. Token still active for 10 min total. |
| Submission window | 30 minutes from invoice | 10 minutes from token mint. Mid-form expiry redirects to timeout page. |
| Anti-spam | Single-use token (inherent) | Single-use token (inherent) |
| Product section source | MVP: auto from kiosk/zone config set in admin panel. Post-MVP: auto from POS SKU data. Customer never selects manually. | Auto from kiosk config (zone knows its section). Customer never selects manually. |

