## 8. Customer-facing flow

### 8.1 Billing zone flow (3 screens, 5-7 taps, <45 seconds)

**Zone and product section are pre-configured in admin panel. Customer never selects them.**

1. **QR scan**: Customer receives QR on printed invoice after purchase. QR encodes `zone_id` + `token_id`. Zone config (including product section) is resolved server-side on form load. Customer scans with phone camera. Opens mobile browser.
2. **Token validation** (invisible): Server checks token is active and not expired. Resolves zone details (zone_type, product_section) from zone config. On failure: friendly error screen (dead end, no form).
3. **Screen 1 — Demographics** (optional): Gender (4 pill options) + age group (4 pill options). Skip button always visible. Skipping sets both to null.
4. **Screen 2 — Emoji ratings**: Single screen, all 4 rows visible.
   - Top: store name (small) + "How was your experience?" (bold headline) + "Tap one per row" (muted subtitle)
   - 4 dimension rows: Pricing / Design / look / Handling / feel / Overall experience
   - Each row: 3 square cards side by side. Each card: coloured emoji icon on top + label below. Green (😊 Happy), Amber (😐 Okay), Red (😞 Unhappy). Unselected = dark card, no highlight. Selected = coloured border + coloured background tint.
   - Visual divider between "Handling / feel" and "Overall experience" rows.
   - Submit button: full-width, below all rows. Disabled state text: "Select all ratings to submit" (grey/muted). Enabled state: button turns green, text changes to "Submit feedback".
   - No numeric counter. Button text is the only completion signal.
5. **Screen 3 — Confirmation**: "Thank you for your feedback!" + "The Chennai Silks". Token status → used. No further action.

**Post-MVP**: POS integration auto-mints token on invoice creation. SKU maps to product_section automatically. Demographics may be pre-populated from POS data.

### 8.2 Browse zone flow (3 screens, 5-7 taps, <30 seconds to scan)

**Zone and product section are pre-configured in admin panel. Customer never selects them.**

1. **Kiosk idle state**: Tablet displays "We'd love your feedback!" + The Chennai Silks + section name + "Tap to share feedback" button + "Your response is anonymous" note. Section name comes from kiosk's zone config.
2. **Kiosk QR state**: On tap, API mints token (10-min TTL). Zone config (zone_id + product_section) embedded in token at mint time. QR displayed with live countdown: "Expires in 28s… 27s… 26s…" counting down from 30. When countdown reaches 0: status line switches to "● Expired — returning to welcome" (red dot), kiosk returns to idle after a brief pause. Token stays active for 10 minutes total in case customer scanned just before reset.
3. **Customer scans kiosk QR with phone.**
4. **Token validation** (invisible): Server resolves zone details from token. If expired: timeout page shown. No form.
5. **Screen 1 — Demographics** (optional): Gender (4 pill options) + age group (4 pill options). Skip button always visible. Product section is NOT shown to customer — already in token from kiosk config.
6. **Screen 2 — Emoji ratings**: Same layout as billing. Customer has up to 10 minutes from token mint to submit. If 10-min window elapses mid-form: redirect to timeout page.
7. **Screen 3 — Confirmation**: "Thank you for your feedback!" + "The Chennai Silks". Kiosk detects token consumed via Realtime, returns to idle.

### 8.3 Error states and timeout behaviour

| Condition | Zone | User sees | System behaviour |
|-----------|------|----------|-----------------|
| Token expired on load (billing) | Billing | Timeout page: "Your feedback window has closed. Purchased customers have 30 minutes from billing." | No form. Dead end. |
| Token expired on load (browse) | Browse | Timeout page: "Your feedback window has closed. Please request a new QR at the kiosk." | No form. Dead end. |
| Token expires mid-form (browse) | Browse | Redirect to timeout page: "Time is up! You had 10 minutes to submit. Please request a new QR at the kiosk." | Form is abandoned. Token already expired. Dead end. |
| Token expires mid-form (billing) | Billing | Timeout page: "Your feedback window has closed. Purchased customers have 30 minutes from billing." | Form is abandoned. Dead end. |
| Token already used — re-scan | Both | Thank you page: "Thanks! We have already received your feedback." | Friendly. No form. |
| Token revoked | Both | "This feedback link is no longer active." | No form. Dead end. |
| Invalid/malformed token | Both | "Something went wrong. Please try scanning the QR again." | Log error. No form. |

**Key rules:**
- Timeout page and thank-you page are distinct screens with different messages.
- Timeout = token expired without submission → show timeout message.
- Already used = token consumed → show thank-you message.
- Mid-form expiry detection: customer form polls token status every 60 seconds. On expiry detected, redirect immediately to timeout page.

