## 10. Admin dashboard — MD / Owner view

### 10.1 Overview dashboard (landing page)
- **Question it answers**: "How is my store doing right now?"
- **Role label**: "MD / Owner view (read-only)" shown persistently top-right
- **Date filter**: pill tabs — Today / This week / This month / Custom. Not a dropdown.
- **Metric cards** (4 equal-width cards in a row):
  - Total submissions + trend vs last period (e.g. "+18% vs last week")
  - Happiness ratio: % happy across all dimensions + "across all dimensions" subtitle
  - Response rate: submissions vs tokens minted (e.g. "247 of 588 tokens used")
  - Top concern: worst-performing dimension name + "X% unhappy this week" subtitle
- **Emotion pulse — all zones combined**: 4 horizontal stacked bars (Pricing, Design, Handling, Overall). Each bar: green (happy) + amber (okay) + red (unhappy). Percentage shown right-aligned = **happy %** always. Colour of percentage text = green if ≥60%, amber if 40-59%, red if <40%.
- **Zone comparison**: two equal side-by-side cards — "Billing zone" and "Browse zone". Each card shows submission count subtitle + mini emotion pulse bars (same 4 dimensions, same colour rules).
- **7-day trend**: dual-axis chart — submission volume (blue area, left axis) + happiness ratio % (green dashed line, right axis). X-axis = Mon–Sun day labels.
- **Visual theme**: dark background throughout (`#1a1a1a` or equivalent). All text light on dark.

### 10.2 Section heatmap
- **Question it answers**: "Which product section needs attention? What do I fix first?"
- Grid: sections (rows) × dimensions (columns). Cell value = happy %. Cell colour = green ≥60% happy, amber 40-59%, red <40%.
- Clickable cells: drill into section-dimension detail (demographic split, trend, zone breakdown)
- Auto-sorted "Top concerns" list below the grid: worst section-dimension pairs ranked by happy % ascending (lowest happy % = rank 1)
- Filters: by section, by zone, by date

**Top concerns list format** (per item):
- Numbered badge: ①②③
- Title: `{Section} — {dimension}` e.g. "Fabrics — pricing"
- Description line: hardcoded template string based on section + dimension combination. See insight templates below.
- Happy % shown right-aligned in red text

**Insight template rules** (hardcoded, MVP):
- Template is chosen by: `dimension` + happy % band (under 40% = red, 40-59% = amber)
- Templates per dimension:

| Dimension | Red template (<40% happy) | Amber template (40-59% happy) |
|-----------|--------------------------|-------------------------------|
| pricing | "Only {happy}% happy. {unhappy}% actively unhappy. {count} submissions." | "Only {happy}% happy. Pricing perceived as high. {count} submissions." |
| design | "Only {happy}% happy. {unhappy}% unhappy with appearance. {count} submissions." | "Only {happy}% happy. Design getting mixed reactions. {count} submissions." |
| handling | "Only {happy}% happy. {unhappy}% unhappy. Customers may dislike fabric feel." | "Only {happy}% happy. Handling needs attention. {count} submissions." |
| overall | "Only {happy}% happy overall. {unhappy}% left dissatisfied. {count} submissions." | "Only {happy}% happy overall. {count} submissions." |

- If a section has the highest submission count among red cells: append " ({count} submissions — highest volume)."
- All `{happy}`, `{unhappy}`, `{count}` values are runtime-substituted from query results.
- Templates live in `en.json` under `heatmap.insights.*` keys. No template logic in components.

### 10.3 Trend analysis
- **Question it answers**: "Is sentiment improving? Did my last change work?"
- Sentiment timeline: daily/weekly happiness ratio per dimension (line chart)
- Before/after comparison: pick two date ranges, side-by-side bars
- Volume vs sentiment: dual-axis (submission count + happiness overlay)
