## 11. User stories with acceptance criteria

### MUST HAVE — Ship day one

#### S-C1: Customer submits feedback via billing zone QR
**Role**: Customer | **Priority**: Must Have

> **Note**: Product section is pre-configured in the admin panel and resolved server-side from zone config. The customer never sees or selects a product section.

- **Given** a customer has a printed invoice with a valid QR code
  **When** they scan the QR with their phone camera
  **Then** the mobile browser opens the feedback form with token validated server-side

- **Given** the token is valid and active
  **When** the form loads
  **Then** demographics screen appears with optional gender and age group pill selectors and a visible skip button

- **Given** demographics completed or skipped
  **When** customer proceeds
  **Then** emoji rating screen shows all 4 rows on a single screen with submit disabled until all selected. No product section selection screen is shown — product_section is resolved server-side from zone config.

- **Given** all 4 ratings selected and submit tapped
  **When** API saves the feedback record
  **Then** token status is set to 'used', confirmation screen shows "Thank you for your feedback!" with The Chennai Silks name

#### S-C2: Customer submits feedback via browse zone kiosk QR
**Role**: Customer | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a kiosk tablet displays the idle welcome screen in a store section
  **When** a customer taps "Tap to share feedback"
  **Then** the kiosk mints a fresh single-use token via API and displays a QR code with a **30-second countdown timer**. The token itself remains active for 10 minutes total after minting.

- **Given** the customer scans the kiosk QR with their phone
  **When** the form loads
  **Then** demographics screen appears (optional). Product section is NOT shown — auto-populated from kiosk zone config

- **Given** demographics completed or skipped
  **When** customer proceeds
  **Then** emoji rating screen shows all 4 rows on a single screen

- **Given** all 4 ratings selected and submit tapped
  **When** API saves the feedback record
  **Then** token status set to 'used', kiosk returns to idle state, confirmation shows on phone

#### S-C3: Customer sees correct message based on token state
**Role**: Customer | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a customer opens a form URL with an expired token (timeout, billing zone)
  **When** the page loads
  **Then** timeout page shown: "Your feedback window has closed. Purchased customers have 30 minutes from billing." No form rendered.

- **Given** a customer opens a form URL with an expired token (timeout, browse zone)
  **When** the page loads
  **Then** timeout page shown: "Your feedback window has closed. Please request a new QR at the kiosk." No form rendered.

- **Given** a customer is mid-form and the 10-minute browse token expires
  **When** the form detects token expiry (polling every 60 seconds)
  **Then** customer is redirected to timeout page: "Time is up! You had 10 minutes to submit. Please request a new QR at the kiosk."

- **Given** a customer is mid-form and the 30-minute billing token expires
  **When** the form detects token expiry
  **Then** customer is redirected to timeout page: "Your feedback window has closed. Purchased customers have 30 minutes from billing."

- **Given** a customer scans an already-used token (re-scan, both zones)
  **When** the form URL loads
  **Then** thank-you page shown: "Thanks! We have already received your feedback." Friendly. No form rendered.

- **Given** a customer tries to submit on a form whose token is already used (double-tap submit)
  **When** the submit API call returns token-already-used error
  **Then** customer sees thank-you page: "Thanks! We have already received your feedback."

- **Given** a customer scans a revoked token
  **When** the form URL loads
  **Then** message shown: "This feedback link is no longer active." No form rendered.

- **Given** a customer opens the form URL without logging in
  **When** the page loads
  **Then** no authentication prompt appears. Form loads directly.

#### S-C4: Kiosk auto-resets after 30-second QR display window
**Role**: System (Kiosk) | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a kiosk is displaying a QR code with a 30-second countdown
  **When** the 30-second timer expires without the QR being scanned
  **Then** the kiosk returns to idle welcome screen. The token remains active for its full 10-minute TTL in case the customer scanned just before reset.

- **Given** a kiosk QR is scanned and feedback is submitted
  **When** the token status changes to 'used'
  **Then** the kiosk detects consumption via Supabase Realtime and returns to idle immediately.

#### S-C5: Billing zone token auto-expires after 30 minutes
**Role**: System | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a billing zone token is minted and status is active
  **When** 30 minutes elapse without a feedback submission
  **Then** the expire-tokens cron function sets token status to 'expired'

- **Given** a purchased customer tries to open their invoice QR after 30 minutes
  **When** the form URL loads
  **Then** timeout page is shown with the billing zone timeout message. No form rendered.

#### S-C6: Browse zone token auto-expires after 10 minutes
**Role**: System | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a browse zone token is minted when customer taps the kiosk
  **When** 10 minutes elapse without a feedback submission
  **Then** the expire-tokens cron function sets token status to 'expired'

- **Given** a browse zone customer has the form open at the 10-minute mark
  **When** the form's 60-second status poll detects expiry
  **Then** the customer is immediately redirected to the timeout page

#### S-A1: Store Admin configures zones
**Role**: Store Admin | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a Store Admin is logged in with 2FA
  **When** they create or edit a zone
  **Then** they can set zone name, zone type (billing/browse), product section (for browse), and token TTL

- **Given** a zone config is saved
  **When** new tokens are minted for that zone
  **Then** tokens use the updated TTL and zone settings

#### S-A2: Store Admin views zone dashboard
**Role**: Store Admin | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a Store Admin is logged in
  **When** they open the dashboard
  **Then** zone-specific metrics are shown: total submissions, rating breakdowns by dimension, product section distribution, and time-based trends

#### S-A3: MD/Owner views cross-zone comparison
**Role**: MD / Owner | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** an MD is logged in with read-only access
  **When** they open the dashboard
  **Then** they see side-by-side metrics for billing and browse zones with cross-zone comparison charts, section heatmap, and trend analysis

#### S-A4: Data governance and privacy
**Role**: System | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** a feedback submission arrives
  **When** it is stored
  **Then** only non-PII fields are saved. No device fingerprints, IP addresses, or personal identifiers stored. RBAC enforced via Supabase RLS.

#### S-A5: MVP deployment scope
**Role**: System | **Priority**: Must Have

- **Given** the system is deployed for MVP
  **When** all components are running
  **Then** one branch (The Chennai Silks), two zones, kiosk app, customer form, and admin dashboard are all operational

### SHOULD HAVE — Sprint 2-3

#### S-B1: Store Admin exports CSV
**Role**: Store Admin / MD | **Priority**: Should Have

- **Given** an admin or MD requests a data export
  **When** export is triggered from the dashboard
  **Then** a CSV file downloads with aggregated metrics, non-PII only, filtered by date range and zone

